C was invented to write an operating system called UNI.

C is a successor of D launguage which was introduced arround the early 1970s.

The launguage was formalized in 1988 by the American National Standard Institute (ANSI).

The UNIX OS was totally written in C.

Today C is the most widely used and popular system programming Launguage.

Most of the state-of-the-art software have been implemented using C.

Today's most popular Linux OS and ROBMS MySQL have been written in C. 

